fr.csvbang.annotation
Annotation Type CsvType

@Target(value=TYPE)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Inherited
@Documented
public @interface CsvType

A type which map a CSV file

0.0.1
Author:
Tony EMMA

asynchronousWriter

public abstract boolean asynchronousWriter
True if you want to write file asynchronously. By default false.

You can define the number of thread dedicate to write file in FactoryCsvWriter. By default the number of thread is the number of processor divide by 3. If you create several files in the same time, the thread will be share for each files.

Returns:
True if you want to write asynchronously
Since:
0.0.1
Default:
false

header

public abstract boolean header
Display the header on the first line. By default false. The header is generated with the name of field. If no name is defined for a field, we take the property name or method name

True or false

false

fileName

public abstract java.lang.String fileName

You can define a static file name.

It is not required. You could define dynamically the filename in Factory.

It is possible to mix configuration. For example you can define dynamically the directory with the factory and a static file name with this annotation.

If a file is defined by factory, it overrides the file created by the annotation

By default no static filename defined

Returns:
the file name
Since:
0.0.1
See Also:
FactoryCsvWriter
Default:
""

append

public abstract boolean append

True if you want to append csv data to a file (if it exist). If the file doesn't exist, it create a new file.

False, if you already want to create a new file. By default, it's false.

Returns:
True if you want to append csv data to a file.
Since:
0.0.1
Default:
false
